ACT:
 Income Tax Act, 1961, Sections 73 and 75-Scope of - Losses in speculation business-A registered firm is not entitled to have its loses in speculation business carried forward for set off against future porfits in speculation business. Any such loss shall be apportioned between the partners of the firm and they (the partners) alone shall be entitled to have the amount of the loss set off and carried froward for set off under Section 73.
 
